It's true to say a small increment has small adverse effect, but it is also true that decentralisation is in a very weak state today.
Harm is incremental but offset by scalability improvements in segwit. It would reduce the problem if network decentralisation were improved.
It's a trade-off, see bathtub curve from @ tdryja. Still no excuse to delay on chain scale nor lightning, and do further on & off chain work.
Decentralisation is how Bitcoin bootstrapped, without being shutdown, and assures permissionless, censor-resistant, fungible properties.
If people think decentralisation is unimportant they might think that, but it's really not the case: decentralisation trade-offs are clear.
